---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import BuyCta from '../../../components/BuyCta.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import FAQ from '../../../components/FAQ.astro';
import { articleSchema, breadcrumbSchema, faqSchema, productReviewSchema } from '../../../lib/schema';

const title = 'McCulloch MHT 5622 Review - Petrol Hedge Trimmer Meets Mower (2026)';
const description = "McCulloch MHT 5622 ride-on mower review. Research-led assessment of this budget ride-on - cut quality, reliability and value for UK lawns.";
const path = '/reviews/mcculloch-mht-5622/';
const datePublished = '2026-05-10';

const crumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'Ride-on lawn mowers', url: '/ride-on-lawn-mowers/' },
  { name: 'McCulloch MHT 5622 review', url: path },
];

const faqs = [
  { q: 'Is the McCulloch MHT 5622 any good?', a: 'It\'s a solid budget ride-on from a brand with genuine heritage. The Briggs & Stratton engine is reliable, the 56 cm deck is adequate for lawns up to 2,000 m², and it\'s one of the cheapest ride-ons worth buying in the UK.' },
  { q: 'What engine does the McCulloch MHT 5622 use?', a: 'Briggs & Stratton 190cc single-cylinder four-stroke. Recoil start, OHV. Proven engine with widely available parts.' },
  { q: 'How big a lawn can it handle?', a: 'Up to about 2,000 m² comfortably. Beyond that you\'ll want a wider deck or a proper garden tractor like the John Deere X167.' },
];

const schema = [
  breadcrumbSchema(crumbs),
  articleSchema({ headline: title, description, url: path, datePublished, dateModified: '2026-06-05' }),
  faqSchema(faqs),
  productReviewSchema({ name: 'McCulloch MHT 5622', brand: 'McCulloch', description, rating: 3.9, url: path, datePublished, dateModified: '2026-06-05', image: '/images/top_8_large_lawnmowers.webp', priceLow: 1300, priceHigh: 1700, reviewBody: 'Budget ride-on with a Briggs & Stratton engine. Does the job on medium UK lawns without the premium price tag.' }),
];
---
<BaseLayout {title} {description} {schema}>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-10">
    <Breadcrumbs items={crumbs} />

    <header class="mb-8">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-grass-700 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">Research-led review · Updated May 2026</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-soil-900 leading-tight">McCulloch MHT 5622 Review</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-slate-500 text-sm">By The Best Mowers UK · Research-led assessment from specs and verified owner reviews</p>
    </header>

    <aside class="bg-grass-50 border-l-4 border-grass-700 rounded-r-lg p-5 mb-10">
      <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4 mb-3">
        <div>
          <p class="text-xs font-bold text-grass-700 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Our verdict</p>
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-soil-900">3.9 / 5</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-right text-sm">
          <p class="font-semibold text-soil-900">£1,499 RRP</p>
          <p class="text-slate-500">Budget ride-on option</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        A no-frills ride-on for people who need to cover 1,000-2,000 m² without spending £3,000. The Briggs & Stratton engine is the star - everything else is adequate rather than impressive, which is exactly what you'd expect at this price.
      </p>
          <BuyCta name="McCulloch MHT 5622" rrp="£1,499" />
    </aside>

    <img src="/images/top_8_large_lawnmowers.webp" alt="Budget ride-on lawn mower on a UK lawn" width="900" height="506" class="w-full rounded-xl my-6 object-cover" loading="eager" fetchpriority="high" />

    <div class="prose-mowers">
      <h2>Specs</h2>
      <table>
        <tbody>
          <tr><th>Engine</th><td>Briggs & Stratton 190cc OHV</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Cutting width</th><td>56 cm</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Cut heights</th><td>5 positions, 30-80 mm</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Drive</th><td>Rear-wheel transmatic</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Collection</th><td>200 L rear collector</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Weight</th><td>142 kg</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>What owners praise</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>The engine</strong> - Briggs & Stratton is the safe choice at this price point. Starts reliably, parts are everywhere.</li>
        <li><strong>The price</strong> - one of the cheapest ride-ons worth recommending in the UK.</li>
        <li><strong>200 L collector</strong> - big enough to do a full mow without emptying on a 1,000 m² lawn.</li>
        <li><strong>Simple controls</strong> - nothing to confuse you. Lever for speed, lever for blade, lever for height. Done.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>The drawbacks</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>56 cm deck is narrow for a ride-on</strong> - you'll do more passes than on a 96 cm+ tractor.</li>
        <li><strong>Build quality is basic</strong> - plastic dashboard, thin seat. Functional, not premium.</li>
        <li><strong>Turning circle is wide</strong> - not ideal for gardens with lots of obstacles or tight corners.</li>
        <li><strong>No mulching option</strong> - collect or side-discharge only.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How it compares</h2>
      <p>
        The <a href="/reviews/mountfield-1538m-sd/">Mountfield 1538M-SD</a> at £2,499 is the next step up - wider deck, better build, Stiga engine. The <a href="/reviews/john-deere-x167/">John Deere X167</a> at £3,299 is the premium choice with a 20-year working life. The McCulloch wins purely on price.
      </p>

      <h2>Who should buy it</h2>
      <p>
        Budget-conscious UK homeowners with 1,000-2,000 m² who need a ride-on but can't justify £2,500+. First-time ride-on buyers moving up from a self-propelled petrol.
      </p>
      <p>
        Don't buy it if your lawn is over 2,500 m² (deck is too narrow), if you want mulching, or if you value build quality - spend more on the Mountfield or John Deere.
      </p>
    </div>

    <FAQ {faqs} />
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
